grep -w "name" file -> Search for exact word name

-i -> ignore case and display name in file
-n -> display line number of the search result
-B 4 -> display 4 lines before the match
-A 4 -> display 4 lines after the match
-C 2 -> display 2 lines before and after the match
-r -> recursive seatch the match in all the subdirectories

-l -> display the files with matches and not the matches itself
-c -> count number of matches found

-P -> for using regular expression perl gnu

grep -P "\d{3}-\d{3}-\d{3}" file -> Search for pattern like: 111-012-124
